        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 8:21PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 821 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bangor, or 8 miles west of Cleveland, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hayden, Nectar, and Bangor.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
